[0.464, "o", "\u001b[1m\r\n=== AegisData T2 demo (mode=stub, aid=agent-demo-ba85f2bb) ===\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  No ANTHROPIC_API_KEY found вЂ” using hardcoded 5-call scenario.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1m\r\nTool-call verdicts:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.321, "o", "  1. \u001b[1mread_file\u001b[0m            в†’ \u001b[33mREQUIRE_APPROVAL\u001b[0m atmu=\u001b[2mcommitted\u001b[0m (The immediate tool call (read_file) is safe and routine, but the declared plan contains multiple high-risk operations: shell execution, large data write (5GB), and financial transaction ($500). The plan scope far exceeds the current operation and suggests potential privilege escalation or data exfiltration intent. Approval needed to validate legitimacy of downstream operations.)\r\n"]
[3.450, "o", "  2. \u001b[1mwrite_file\u001b[0m           в†’ \u001b[33mREQUIRE_APPROVAL\u001b[0m atmu=\u001b[2mcommitted\u001b[0m (Multi-step plan contains escalating operations with unclear scope. Initial write_file call is safe, but plan includes: shell execution (privilege/code injection risk), 5GB blob write (resource exhaustion), and financial transaction ($500 transfer). Insufficient context on legitimacy of later steps and cost forecast ($0.01) suggests significant resource commitment. Requires human review of full plan intent.)\r\n"]
[0.697, "o", "  3. \u001b[1mexecute_shell\u001b[0m        в†’ \u001b[31mBLOCK\u001b[0m          atmu=\u001b[2maborted\u001b[0m (dangerous pattern: \\brm\\s+-rf\\s+/)\r\n"]
[0.674, "o", "  4. \u001b[1mwrite_file\u001b[0m           в†’ \u001b[33mREQUIRE_APPROVAL\u001b[0m atmu=\u001b[2mcommitted\u001b[0m (forecasted_cost_to_completion 5.0000 > budget 1.0000)\r\n"]
[0.668, "o", "  5. \u001b[1mtransfer_funds\u001b[0m       в†’ \u001b[33mREQUIRE_APPROVAL\u001b[0m atmu=\u001b[2mcommitted\u001b[0m (blast radius 10 >= 7)\r\n\u001b[1m\r\nVerdict tally:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  \u001b[32mALLOW\u001b[0m            0\r\n  \u001b[31mBLOCK\u001b[0m            1\r\n  \u001b[33mREQUIRE_APPROVAL\u001b[0m 4\r\n"]
